filled_sections.text:
IN THE COURT OF THE {{COURT_NAME}}
AT {{COURT_PLACE}}

O.S. No. {{SUIT_NUMBER}} / {{SUIT_YEAR}}

The Defendant resides and carries on business at {{DEFENDANT_ADDRESS}} within the local limits of this Court's territorial jurisdiction. The advance amount of Rs. 20,00,000 was paid by the Plaintiff on {{ADVANCE_PAYMENT_DATE}} by transfer from the Plaintiff's bank account with {{BANK_NAME}} at {{BANK_BRANCH}} to the Defendant's account, as evidenced by Annexure B. The Agreement was executed on {{AGREEMENT_DATE}} at {{AGREEMENT_PLACE}}, which lies within the territorial reach of this Court. The cause of action first arose on {{CAUSE_OF_ACTION_DATE}} at {{CAUSE_OF_ACTION_PLACE}} when the Defendant defaulted in performing its obligation to refund the advance, resulting in total failure of consideration under Section 65 of the Indian Contract Act. Therefore, this Court has territorial jurisdiction to adjudicate the dispute.

Pecuniary jurisdiction: The Plaintiff seeks Rs. 20,00,000, which falls within the monetary limits of this District Court.

